# OverLanguage: ZipToApp — AI-native zip → .app bundle renderer
# Content-aware binary analysis, smart resource classification, entitlements inference,
# dependency graph, AI-readable manifest, self-healing validation, bundle optimization

workflow: ZipToApp
intent: take a .zip archive and render it into a valid, optimized, AI-readable macOS .app bundle — detecting binary type by magic bytes, classifying resources by content, inferring entitlements from capability hints, building a dependency graph, emitting an AI manifest, self-healing structural issues, and optimizing bundle layout

step 1: read zip archive → zip_contents
step 2: validate zip structure → zip_validated
step 3: extract zip to staging → staging_dir
step 4: analyze binary content → binary_analysis
step 5: detect executable entry → exec_entry
step 6: classify resources → resource_map
step 7: infer entitlements → entitlements
step 8: build dependency graph → dependency_graph
step 9: generate Info.plist → info_plist
step 10: assemble .app bundle → app_bundle
step 11: set executable permissions → exec_perms
step 12: ad-hoc code sign → code_signature
step 13: emit AI manifest → ai_manifest
step 14: self-heal bundle validation → heal_report
step 15: compute SHA256 of bundle → bundle_hash
step 16: write chained receipt → signed_receipt

artifact: app_bundle
artifact: ai_manifest
artifact: signed_receipt
receipt: SHA256 chained from step 1 through step 16, merkle root over bundle hash + plist + signature + AI manifest
value: any zip archive rendered into a launchable, AI-readable, self-healing macOS .app bundle — no Xcode required, no human intervention needed
